\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nys1665703528633.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nys1665703528633.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nys1665703528633.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nys1665703528633\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Debugger Browser to view the structure and ProcScript modules of components\n      and Global ProcScript library. You can also toggle breakpoints in a ProcScript module, watch\n      fields and variables, or change their values. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nys1665703528633__p_d175532e1_d175533e1_d175534e1\">The type of object determines what is displayed. By default, the current component is open. You can open another component or global ProcScript for examination.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nys1665703528633__section_p1l_lj3_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d576450e56\">Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following fields are available:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"nys1665703528633__ul_mw3_mj3_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nys1665703528633__li_d53495e1_d53496e1_d53497e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span>—structure of the\n               current component or Global ProcScript, showing entities and fields, nonempty\n               triggers, local ProcScript modules, and a list of component or global variables. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nys1665703528633__li_d53498e1_d53499e1_d53500e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Trigger / Module</span>— contents\n               of the ProcScript module for the item selected in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> field. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nys1665703528633__section_rch_gk3_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d576450e81\">Structure</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Displays the tree structure of the currently open component or global ProcScript.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Tree items for Debugger structure types</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1__entry__1\"> Structure type </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1__entry__2\"> Tree items </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1__entry__1\"> Component </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1__entry__2\">The entities and fields, all nonempty triggers,\n                        local ProcScript modules, and a list of component variables. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1__entry__1\"> Library </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nys1665703528633__table_d18479e1_d18480e1_d18481e1__entry__2\">The global ProcScript module currently open and\n                        a list of all global variables in the library. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nys1665703528633__section_dsf_kk3_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d576450e136\">Trigger / Module</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Displays the contents of the ProcScript module for the item selected in the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> field.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nys1665703528633__section_nzc_rfh_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d576450e148\">Debugger Browser information</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information about the Debugger Browser, refer to: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gjf1665702773980.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gjf1665702773980.html\" title=\"Navigate to specific ProcScript modules in components or global ProcScript using the Debugger Browser, and use the browser to set breakpoints and watches.\">Browsing ProcScript Modules in the Uniface Debugger</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/epv1665703523533.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with watches</a><p>Add watches from the debugger main window or from the browser.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vsb1665703523691.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Updating fields, variables, or watch values</a><p>Update watch fields, variables, or values.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614921\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614921\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Debugger Browser Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Use the Debugger Browser to view the structure and ProcScript modules of components and Global ProcScript library. You can also toggle breakpoints in a ProcScript module, watch fields and variables, or change their values. The type of object determines what is displayed. By default, the current component is open. You can open another component or global ProcScript for examination. Fields The following fields are available: Structure —structure of the current component or Global ProcScript, showing entities and fields, nonempty triggers, local ProcScript modules, and a list of component or global variables. Trigger / Module — contents of the ProcScript module for the item selected in the Structure field. Structure Displays the tree structure of the currently open component or global ProcScript. Table 1. Tree items for Debugger structure types Structure type Tree items Component The entities and fields, all nonempty triggers, local ProcScript modules, and a list of component variables. Library The global ProcScript module currently open and a list of all global variables in the library. Trigger / Module Displays the contents of the ProcScript module for the item selected in the Structure field. Debugger Browser information For more information about the Debugger Browser, refer to: Browsing ProcScript Modules in the Uniface Debugger . Related Links Working with watches Add watches from the debugger main window or from the browser. Updating fields, variables, or watch values Update watch fields, variables, or values. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}